{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2509;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\cf1\b\f0\fs20 The user can move and stretch, move columns, and otherwise customize Forms according to what they need. \par
\par
Saving those customizations is a nice feature, and fortunately it is easy in Magic. All you need to do is specify \cf2 Persistent form state \cf1 for each Form.\par
\par
Note: the Form State Persistency works in Runtime, but not in the Studio. To test this, you need to use the Runtime (RTE) version of Magic.\par
